Package: networkR
Title: Flexible Bayesian Network Pipelines for Experimental Studies
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Author: NetworkR Authors
Maintainer: NetworkR Authors <packages@example.com>
Description: Provides a configurable pipeline for Bayesian network and staged
    event tree structure learning in factorial and repeated-measures studies.
    The package supports panel ingestion, derived design variables, predictive
    mean matching imputation, discretization, variable-order constraint
    construction, parallelized bootstrap stability estimation, structure
    comparison, and ggraph-based network and event tree visualization.
    Supports stagedtrees (default) and bnlearn as interchangeable backends.
